{
  "texts": [
    "This makes their use in pragmatic policymaking settings very difficult.",
    "To remedy this situation, the research community is working on explainable AI (XAI) techniques, which aim at building AI systems that are transparent (i.e., \"glass box\" models) and at explaining how black box algorithms work.",
    "XAI techniques can be used to explain to policymakers why an AI system recommends a specific policy decision.",
    "This is particularly important for the practical deployment of AI systems in policy development settings as policymakers won't use AI systems that cannot understand how they work.",
    "XAI is also a key prerequisite for the transparency of ML-based policy decisions, as these decisions cannot be transparent unless stakeholders understand how AI systems recommend specific decisions."
  ]
}